# Knowledge Base Configuration

# Absolute path or "~/..." to the knowledge base root directory.
# The server validates all tool paths against this root and rejects any traversal outside it.
MCP_KB_FS_ROOT_PATH=~/your-kb

# Maximum access level to register. One of: read, write, destructive.
# Levels nest: `read` registers only read-only tools (the default — least
# privilege); `write` adds non-destructive mutations; `destructive` adds
# delete/overwrite tools (e.g. kb_note_write). Each tool's level is derived
# from its MCP annotations (readOnlyHint / destructiveHint), not its name;
# see src/utils/access-level.ts.
# MCP_KB_FS_ACCESS_LEVEL=destructive
